  "title": "Per-message JP translation reveal in Conversation",
  "description": "Add a lightweight 'JPши│' (translate) toggle button to each assistant bubble in the Conversation chat so a learner who can't fully understand the English reply can reveal a Japanese translation inline without breaking the conversation flow. This addresses a real friction point: today, learners who don't understand a reply have no choice but to guess or abandon the session.\n\nScope (small, low-risk, no schema/migration changes, no dashboard touch):\n\n1. Backend endpoint тАФ `app/routers/conversation.py`: add `POST /api/conversation/translate` that accepts `{ text: str }` (Pydantic model, max 1000 chars, non-empty after strip) and returns `{ translation: str }`. Implementation calls `copilot_client` with a tiny dedicated system prompt added to `app/prompts.py` (e.g. `TRANSLATE_TO_JP_SYSTEM = 'Translate the given English sentence to natural, concise Japanese. Output only the translation, no quotes or commentary.'`). Use a short temperature (0.2) and small max_tokens cap (~200) so the call is fast (<2s). Return 422 on empty text and 400 on overly long input. No DB writes тАФ translations are ephemeral.\n\n2. Frontend тАФ `frontend/src/pages/Conversation.tsx` (and the assistant message component if separate): for each assistant message render a small ghost button `ЁЯЗпЁЯЗ╡ JPши│` next to the existing copy/replay controls. On click: call the new endpoint (with a per-message loading spinner), then display the translation in a muted secondary line below the original English (e.g. `<div class='translation'>` with smaller font and `--color-text-muted`). Once fetched, cache in component state keyed by message id so re-toggling is instant. Button toggles between `JPши│уВТшбичд║` and `JPши│уВТщЪауБЩ`. Make sure the translation text is NOT passed to `useSpeechSynthesis` (only the English original is spoken).\n\n3. Styling тАФ add a `.message-translation` rule (works in both light & dark themes via existing CSS variables, contrast тЙе4.5:1).\n\n4. Tests тАФ `tests/unit/test_conversation_translate.py`: test the endpoint with (a) valid English input returns 200 + non-empty translation (mock copilot_client), (b) empty string returns 422, (c) >1000 chars returns 400, (d) copilot failure returns 502/500 with structured error.\n\nFiles to modify (тЙд5):\n- app/routers/conversation.py (add endpoint + Pydantic request/response)\n- app/prompts.py (add TRANSLATE_TO_JP_SYSTEM constant)\n- frontend/src/pages/Conversation.tsx (button + state + render)\n- frontend/src/pages/Conversation.css (or equivalent тАФ translation row style)\n- tests/unit/test_conversation_translate.py (new tests)\n\nNo `database.py` SCHEMA changes, no migrations, no dashboard aggregation changes тАФ avoiding the iter 649 failure pattern. The slice is independently testable (endpoint can be unit-tested with mocked copilot, UI button is a localized addition).",
