Looking at the backlog, only bugs/perf/infra remain, so I'll propose a fresh feature. Recent work has heavily targeted Conversation, Vocabulary, Listening, and Minimal Pairs. Pronunciation page has Trouble Words & missed-word drill but lacks **prosody/stress training**, which is a known gap for fluent speaking. A small, self-contained "Stress Pattern Tap" mini-game fits perfectly: frontend-only, curated client-side data, tests are pure functions + component logic.```json
{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Add Word Stress Tap mini-game to Pronunciation page (prosody training)",
  "description": "Pronunciation practice currently focuses on phoneme accuracy, shadowing, dictation, minimal pairs, and missed-word drills, but English **prosody / word stress** тАФ the single biggest contributor to perceived fluency тАФ is never explicitly trained. Add a new self-contained 'Stress Tap' mini-mode under the Pronunciation page that drills primary-stress placement on multi-syllable words.\n\nUX flow (frontend-only, no backend changes):\n1. Add a new entry `'stress-tap'` to the existing `practiceMode` union in `frontend/src/pages/Pronunciation.tsx` and a card in the mode-selector grid (icon: existing lucide `Activity` or `Volume2`).\n2. New component `frontend/src/components/pronunciation/StressTapDrill.tsx` renders a curated word (e.g., `pho-TO-graph-y`) with each syllable as a tappable pill. The user taps the pill they think carries the primary stress. Feedback shows correct/incorrect, then auto-plays the word via `useSpeechSynthesis` so the user can hear the contrast. A 'Replay slow' button calls TTS at rate 0.7. After a 6-word round, show a summary score.\n3. Curated client-side data lives in `frontend/src/utils/stressPatterns.ts` as `STRESS_WORDS: { word: string; syllables: string[]; stressIndex: number; meaning?: string }[]` (~30 common multi-syllable words with known learner-tricky stress: photography, comfortable, necessary, develop, hotel, hospital, computer, restaurant, banana, tomato, vegetable, etc.). Also export a pure helper `pickStressRound(words, n, seed?)` that returns `n` randomly selected entries (Fisher-Yates with optional seed for testability).\n4. Persist a small per-word accuracy map under `localStorage['stress_tap_stats']` so future rounds bias toward the user's weak words. Helper `selectWeightedRound(words, stats, n)` should weight previously-wrong words ~3├Ч and previously-correct words ~1├Ч.\n\nTests (Vitest, frontend/src/__tests__/):\n- `stressPatterns.test.ts`: verifies `pickStressRound` returns exactly `n` distinct items, is deterministic with a seed, and never returns more than the dataset size; verifies `selectWeightedRound` increases the probability mass of words with prior wrong attempts (seeded run statistics).\n- `StressTapDrill.test.tsx`: renders the component, taps each syllable pill, asserts correct/incorrect feedback styling and that the score increments only on correct taps, and that the round-complete summary shows after N words.\n\nNo backend, no DB, no migration. Files modified тЙд5. Estimated ~1 hour. Diversifies away from Conversation/Vocabulary, fills a real gap (prosody) for the listening/speaking-fluency goal of the app.",
  "files_to_modify": [
    "frontend/src/pages/Pronunciation.tsx",
    "frontend/src/components/pronunciation/StressTapDrill.tsx",
    "frontend/src/utils/stressPatterns.ts",
    "frontend/src/__tests__/stressPatterns.test.ts",
    "frontend/src/__tests__/StressTapDrill.test.tsx"
  ],
  "priority": "high",
  "estimated_complexity": "small"
}
